description: An acquired metabolic disease that characterized by excessive production of acid.

name: myotonic dystrophy type 2
description: A myotonic disease that is characterized by myotonia and progressive, proximal muscle  wasting and weakness affecting the skeletal and smooth muscles of the neck, shoulders, elbows and hips and has_material_basis_in the autosomal dominant inheritance of the CNBP (ZNF9) gene containing an expansion of a CCTG repeat in intron one.

name: X-linked myopathy with excessive autophagy
description: A myopathy that is characterized by childhood onset of progressive muscle weakness and atrophy primarily affecting the proximal muscles in males between 5 and 10 years old, has_material_basis_in mutation in the VMA21 gene on chromosome Xq28.

name: adenylosuccinase lyase deficiency
description: An amino acid metabolic disorder that is characterized by microcephaly, aggressive behavior, cerebellar hypoplasia and seizures, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the ADSL gene resulting in adenylosuccinate lyase deficiency.

name: ARC syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by congenital joint contractures, renal tubular dysfunction, cholestasis, severe failure to thrive, ichthyosis and a defect in platelet alpha-granule biogenesis and that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VPS33B gene or homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VIPAR gene on chromosome 14q24.3.
synonyms: ["Arthrogryposis, renal dysfunction and cholestasis (ARC) syndrome","ARTHROGRYPOSIS, RENAL DYSFUNCTION, AND CHOLESTASIS","Arthrogryposis-renal dysfunction-cholestasis"]

name: Armfield syndrome
description: A syndromic X-linked intellectual disability characterized by intellectual disability, short stature, seizures, and small hands and feet  and in some cases cleft palate or cataracts/glaucoma that has_material_basis_in variation in the chromosomal region Xq28.
synonyms: ["Armfield X-linked mental retardation syndrome","mental retardation syndrome, X-linked, Armfield type","MRXSA","syndromic X-linked mental retardation Armfield type","X-linked intellectual disability, Armfield type"]

name: neuroacanthocytosis
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by characterized by misshapen, spiny red blood cells (acanthocytosis) and neurological abnormalities, especially movement disorders.

name: choreaacanthocytosis
description: A neuroacanthocytosis characterized by progressive neurodegeneration and red cell acanthocytosis, with onset in the third to fifth decade of life and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the VPS13A gene, which encodes chorein, on chromosome 9q21.

name: midface dysplasia
description: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by hypertelorism, a wide nose, vertical midline cleft and encephalocele.

name: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency, nuclear type 1
description: A mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATPAF2 gene on chromosome 17p11.

name: N syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by intellectual disability, deafness, ocular abnormalities, T-cell leukemia, cryptorchidism, hypospadias and spasticity.

name: polycystic liver disease
description: A liver disease that is characterized by the presence of multiple cysts located_in the liver.
synonyms: ["congenital cystic liver disease","congenital hepatic cyst","fibrocystic liver disease"]

name: pheochromocytoma
description: An endocrine organ benign neoplasm that arises within the adrenal medulla, releasing epinephrines and norepinephrines hormones that cause either episodic or persistent high blood pressure.

name: spastic ataxia 1
description: A spastic ataxia characterized by early-onset cerebellar ataxia, spasticity, pyramidal syndrome and peripheral neuropathy, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of heterozygous mutation in the VAMP1 gene on chromosome 12p13.

name: paraganglioma
description: A pheochromocytoma that arises in extraadrenal sympathetic ganglia.

name: rapadilino syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by radial ray defect, patellae hypoplasia, cleft palate, diarrhea, dislocated joints, limb malformations, long nose and normal intelligence, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the DNA helicase gene RECQL4 on chromosome 8q24.

name: schneckenbecken dysplasia
description: An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by hypoplastic iliac bones, hypoplastic vertebral bodies, short ribs and broad long bones, prenatally lethal, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the SLC35D1 gene on chromosome 1p31.

name: non-syndromic X-linked intellectual disability
description: A non-syndromic intellectual disability characterized by a X-linked inheritance pattern.

name: Joubert syndrome
description: A ciliopathy that is characterized by congenital malformation of the brainstem and agenesis or hypoplasia of the cerebellar vermis leading to an abnormal respiratory pattern, nystagmus, hypotonia, ataxia, and delay in achieving motor milestones.

name: Meckel syndrome
description: A ciliopathy that is characterized by renal cystic dysplasia, occipital encephalocele, polydactyly (post axial), hepatic developmental defects, and pulmonary hypoplasia.

name: hydrolethalus syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by mulitple fetal developmental defects including polydactyly and central nervous system malformations that results from a single amino acid mutation of D211G of the HYLS1 gene which plays a central role in cilia formation.

name: Opitz-GBBB syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by hypertelorism, hypospadias, and additional midline defects.

name: Ogden syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by postnatal growth failure, severely delayed psychomotor development, variable dysmorphic features, and hypotonia and has_material_basis_in X-linked recessive or X-linked dominant mutation in the NAA10 gene on chromosome Xq28.
synonyms: ["N-alpha-acetyltransferase","N-terminal acetyltransferase deficiency","OGDNS","X-linked Malformation and Infantile Lethality Syndrome"]

name: Zollinger-Ellison syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by the development of a one or more tumors (gastrinoma) in the pancreas, duodenum, or both that secrete excessive levels of gastrin, a hormone that stimulates production of acid by the stomach.

name: secondary progressive multiple sclerosis
description: A multiple sclerosis that is characterised by a worsening of disability, rather than by relapses followed by recovery, which progressively worsens until a steady progression of disability replaces the cycles of attacks.

name: primary progressive multiple sclerosis
description: A multiple sclerosis that is characterized by steady worsening of neurologic functioning, without any distinct relapses or periods of remission. The rate of progression may vary over time, with occasional plateaus or temporary improvements, but the progression is continuous.

name: progressive relapsing multiple sclerosis
description: A multiple sclerosis that is characterized by steadily worsening symptoms and attacks during periods of remission with disease progression from the onset.

name: iridogoniodysgenesis syndrome
description: An iris disease that is characterized by the iris stroma being hypoplastic resulting from abnormalities in the differentiation of the anterior segment structures and increased values of intraocular pressure and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutations in the PITX2 gene.

name: juvenile polyposis syndrome
description: A gastrointestinal system disease that is characterized by predisposition to hamartomatous benign polyps in the gastrointestinal tract, specifically in the stomach, small intestine, colon, and rectum.

name: proximal symphalangism
description: A syndrome that is characterized by ankylosis of the proximal interphalangeal joints, carpal and tarsal bone fusion, and conductive deafness.

name: tarsal-carpal coalition syndrome
description: A dysostosis that is characterized by fusion of the carpals, tarsals, and phalanges, short first metacarpals causing brachydactyly; and humeroradial fusion.

name: fibular hypoplasia and complex brachydactyly
description: A bone development disease that is characterised by severe reduction or absence of the fibula and complex brachydactyly.

name: persistent Mullerian duct syndrome
description: A pseudohermaphroditism that is characterized by the persistence of Mullerian duct derivatives (i.e. uterus, cervix, fallopian tubes and upper two thirds of vagina) in a phenotypically and karyotypically male.

name: multiple cutaneous and mucosal venous malformations
description: A vein disease that is characterized by multiple bluish cutaneous or mucosal venous lesions.

name: short QT syndrome
description: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by heart arrhythmia defined as a short QT interval on an EKG (less than 300 ms) that does not significantly change with heart rate, tall and peaked T waves, and a structurally normal heart.

name: multiple synostoses syndrome
description: A dysostosis that is characterized by premature joint ankylosis and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inhertitance.

name: cone dystrophy
description: A retinal disease that is characterized by the loss of cone cells, the photoreceptors responsible for both central and color vision.

name: achalasia microcephaly syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by microcephaly, intellectual deficit and early onset symptoms of achalasia (abnormal enlargement of the esophagus, impaired peristalsis, cardiospasm, recurrent vomiting and respiratory infections).

name: peroxisomal acyl-CoA oxidase deficiency
description: A peroxisomal disease that is characterized by hypotonia and seizures in the neonatal period and neurological regression in early infancy.

name: cerebral creatine deficiency syndrome
description: An amino acid metabolic disorder that is characterized by mental retardation, severe speech delay, behavioral abnormalities and seizures, has_material_basis_in mutation in the creatine transporter gene on chromosome Xq28.

name: guanidinoacetate methyltransferase deficiency
description: A cerebral creatine deficiency syndrome that is characterized by severe intellectual disability, seizures, speech problems and involuntary movements, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the GAMT gene on chromosome 19p13.

name: creatine transporter deficiency
description: A cerebral creatine deficiency syndrome that is characterized by mental retardation, severe speech delay, behavioral abnormalities and seizures, has_material_basis_in mutation in the SLC6A8 gene on chromosome Xq28.

name: androgenic alopecia
description: An alopecia that is characterized by M-shaped hair line recession and thinning of hair at the crown of the head in males.

name: Ehlers-Danlos syndrome spondylodysplastic type 2
description: An Ehlers-Danlos syndrome that is characterized by aged appearance, developmental delay, short stature, craniofacial disproportion, generalized osteopenia, defective wound healing, hypermobile joints, hypotonic muscles, and loose but elastic skin and has_material_basis_in compound heterozygous mutation in the B3GALT6 gene.
synonyms: ["Ehlers-Danlos syndrome progeroid type","EHLERS-DANLOS SYNDROME, PROGEROID TYPE, 2"]

name: glioblastoma classical subtype
description: A glioblastoma that is characterized by abnormally high levels of epidermal growth factor receptor and the absence of p53 mutations.

name: glioblastoma proneural subtype
description: A glioblastoma that is characterized by IDH1 and p53 mutations and Platelet Derived Growth Factor A amplification.

name: glioblastoma mesenchymal subtype
description: A glioblastoma that is characterized by the most frequent number of mutation of the Neurofibromin 1 gene.

name: glioblastoma neural subtype
description: A glioblastoma that is characterized by the expression of several gene types that are also typical of the brain's normal, noncancerous nerve cells, or neurons.

name: Kahrizi syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by mental retardation, cataracts, coloboma, kyphosis, and coarse facial features and has_material_basis_in mutation in the SRD5A3 gene.

name: mucopolysaccharidosis IX
description: A mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by a deficiency in hyaluronidase.

name: biotin deficiency
description: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by thinning of the hair (often with loss of hair color), and red scaly rash around the eyes, nose, and mouth.

name: congenital adrenal hyperplasia
description: A steroid inherited metabolic disorder that is characterized by adrenal insufficiency and variable degrees of hyper or hypo androgeny manifestations resulting from steroidogenic enzyme deficiency.

name: spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia, Pakistani type
description: A spondyloepimetaphyseal dysplasia that is characterized by short stature, short and bowed lower limbs, mild brachydactyly, kyphoscoliosis, abnormal gait, enlarged knee joints, precocious osteoarthropathy, and normal intelligence.

name: spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia with congenital joint dislocations
description: A spondyloepiphyseal dysplasia that is characterized by short stature of prenatal onset, joint dislocations (knees, hips, radial heads), club feet, and limitation of range of motion that can involve all large joints.
synonyms: ["CHONDRODYSPLASIA WITH MULTIPLE DISLOCATIONS","CHST3-Related Skeletal Dysplasia","Humero-spinal dysostosis with congenital heart disease","Humerospinal Dysostosis","Humerospinal dysostosis","Kozlowski Celermajer Tink syndrome","Omani Type","Spondyloepiphyseal Dysplasia"]

name: temtamy preaxial brachydactyly syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by brachydactyly, hyperphalangism of digits, facial dysmorphism, dental anomalies, sensorineural hearing loss, delayed motor and mental development, and growth retardation and has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the CHSY1 gene.

name: obsolete eye adnexa disease
description: An eye and adnexa disease that is located_in the adnexa of the eye.

name: urofacial syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by inverted facial expressions in association with a severe and early-onset form of dysfunctional urinary voiding.

name: Stargardt disease
description: An age related macular degeneration that is characterized by progressive vision loss usually to the point of legal blindness.

name: transcobalamin II deficiency
description: A vitamin B12 deficiency that is characterized by a lack of vitamin B12 intestinal absorption resulting from a deficiency in the B12 transport protein TCII.

name: obsolete Matthew-Wood syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by microphthalmia or anophthalmia, pulmonary agenesis, and diaphragmatic defect.

name: atrioventricular block
description: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by the impairment of the conduction between the atria and ventricles of the heart.

name: first-degree atrioventricular block
description: An atrioventricular block that is characterized by prolonged PR interval on electrocardiogram caused by delayed conduction from atria to ventricles through the atrioventricular node.

name: second-degree atrioventricular block
description: An atrioventricular block that is characterized by progressive prolongation of the PR interval on consecutive beats followed by a blocked P wave on electrocardiogram or intermittently non-conducted P waves not preceded by PR changes on electrocardiogram caused by a conduction block between the atria and the ventricles through the atrioventricular node.

name: third-degree atrioventricular block
description: An atrioventricular block that is characterized by bradycardia, hypotension, hemodynamic instability and complete dissociation between P waves and QRS complexes on electrocardiogram caused when conduction fails to propagate from atria to ventricles.

name: sinoatrial node disease
description: A heart conduction disease that is characterized by dysfunction of the impulse-generating (pacemaker) tissue located in the right atrium of the heart which generates normal sinus rhythm.

name: endocardium disease
description: A heart disease that is located_in the innermost layer of tissue that lines the chambers of the heart.

name: tricuspid valve disease
description: A heart valve disease that is characterized by valvular insufficiency or valvular stenosis, located_in tricuspid valve between the right atrium and right ventricle.
synonyms: ["disease of tricuspid valve","RH. tricuspid valve disease","Rheumatic disease of tricuspid valve","Rheumatic tricuspid valve disease","rheumatic tricuspid valve disease","Tricuspid disease"]

name: rheumatic heart disease
description: A heart valve disease that is characterized by repeated inflammation with fibrinous repair caused by an autoimmune reaction to Group A beta-hemolytic streptococci (GAS) that results in valvular damage. The cardinal anatomic changes of the valve include leaflet thickening, commissural fusion, and shortening and thickening of the tendinous cords.

name: artery disease
description: A vascular disease that is located_in an artery.

name: pericardium disease
description: A cardiovascular system disease that is located_in the  fibrous sac surrounding the heart.

name: peripheral artery disease
description: An artery disease that is characterized by build up of plaque in the arteries that carry blood to your head, organs, and limbs.

name: familial encephalopathy with neuroserpin inclusion bodies
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by intraneuronal inclusions of mutant neuroserpin resulting in progressive encephalopathy, dementia and seizures and has_material_basis_in a mutation in the SERPINI1 gene inherited in an in autosomal dominant pattern.

name: pyrimidine metabolic disorder
description: An inherited metabolic disorder involving dysfunction of pyrimidine metabolism.

name: orotic aciduria
description: A pyrimidine metabolic disorder that is characterized by an excessive secretion of orotic acid in urine.

name: CHARGE syndrome
description: A syndrome that is acterized by a pattern of congenital anomalies including choanal atresia and malformations of the heart, inner ear, and retina.

name: generalized dystonia
description: A dystonia that affects most or all of the body.

name: focal dystonia
description: A dystonia that is localized to a specific part of the body.

name: multifocal dystonia
description: A dystonia that involves two or more unrelated body parts.

name: segmental dystonia
description: A dystonia that affects two or more adjacent parts of the body.

name: anismus
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized by the failure of the pelvic floor muscles to relax during defecation.

name: cervical dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized by simultaneous contraction of the agonist and antagonist muscles that control the position of the head contracting during dystonic movement which causes the neck to involuntarily turn to the left, right, upwards, and/or downwards.

name: focal hand dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that affects a single muscle or small group of muscles in the hand resulting from involuntary muscular contractions.

name: oculogyric crisis
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized by a prolonged involuntary upward deviation of the eyes.

name: oromandibular dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized by distortions of the mouth and tongue.

name: spasmodic dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that involves the muscles that control the vocal cords, resulting in strained or breathy speech.

name: cranio-facial dystonia
description: A focal dystonia that is characterized as dystonia that affects the muscles of the head, face, and neck.

name: hemidystonia
description: A multifocal dystonia that involves the arm and leg on the same side of the body.

name: sleep apnea
description: A sleep disorder characterized by repeated cessation and commencing of breathing that repeatedly disrupts sleep.

name: obstructive sleep apnea
description: A sleep apnea that is characterized by repeated collapse and obstruction of the upper airway during sleep, which results in reduced airflow (hypopnea) or complete airflow cessation (apnea), oxygen desaturation, and arousals from sleep.

name: periampullary adenoma
description: An ampulla of Vater neoplasm that is characterized by glandular dysplastic lesion having pre-malignant potential.

name: diabetic encephalopathy
description: A brain disease that is characterized by functional impairment of cognition, cerebral signal conduction, neurotransmission and synaptic plasticity, and underlying structural pathology associated with diabetes.

name: glomerulosclerosis
description: A glomerulonephritis that is characterized by hardening of the glomerulus in the kidney.

name: limb ischemia
description: An ischemia that is characterized by low blood supply to tissues in the limb due to interruption in the arterial blood supply.

name: chronic venous insufficiency
description: A venous insufficiency that is characterized by lower extremity swelling, hyperpigmentation, pruritus and venous ulceration caused by blood pooling in the veins.

name: Muckle-Wells syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by episodic skin rash, arthralgias, and fever associated with late-onset sensorineural deafness and renal amyloidosis that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in NLRP3 on chromosome 1q44.

name: renal fibrosis
description: A kidney disease that is characterized by progressive detrimental connective tissue deposition of the kidney parenchyma leading to deterioration of renal function.

name: oppositional defiant disorder
description: A specific developmental disorder that is characterized by a pattern of angry mood, defiant behavior and vindictiveness in children and adolescents.

name: Perrault syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by sensorineural hearing loss and ovarian failure.

name: Marshall-Smith syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by advanced bone age, failure to thrive, respiratory problems, dysmorphic facial features, and variable mental retardation.

name: hemorrhagic cystitis
description: A cystitis that is characterized by dysuria, hematuria and hemorrhage located_in the lower urinary tract.

name: colorectal adenoma
description: An intestinal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin and is located_in colon and located_in rectum.

name: colorectal adenocarcinoma
description: A colorectal carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: pyometritis
description: A uterine disease that is characterized by inflammation of the uterus and is associated with pus in the uterine cavity.

name: arteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy
description: An anterior ischemic optic neuropathy that is characterized by near-complete vision loss caused by damage to the medium-sized blood vessels supplying the optic nerves following temporal arteritis.

name: non-arteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy
description: An anterior ischemic optic neuropathy that is characterized by near-complete vision loss caused by acute ischemic damage to the optic nerve due to non-inflammatory small vessel disease.
synonyms: ["non-arteritic anterior ischaemic optic neuropathy","nonarteritic anterior ischaemic optic neuropathy","nonarteritic anterior ischemic optic neuropathy"]

name: tongue squamous cell carcinoma
description: A head and neck squamous cell carcinoma that is located_in the tongue.

name: oral squamous cell carcinoma
description: An oral cavity cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: obsolete Jensen syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by sensorineural hearing loss with onset in infancy, followed in adolescence by progressive optic nerve atrophy with loss of vision and in adulthood by progressive dementia.

name: hepatocellular adenoma
description: A liver benign neoplasm that is located_in liver cells and that is composed_of epithelial tissue in which tumor cells form glands or glandlike structures.

name: villous adenoma
description: An adenoma that is located_in the colon and other places in the gastrointestinal tract and sometimes in other parts of the body.

name: pulmonary adenocarcinoma in situ
description: A lung carcinoma in situ that derives_from the distal bronchioles or alveoli that initially exhibit a specific non-invasive growth pattern.

name: fibroma
description: A connective tissue benign neoplasm composed of fibrous or connective tissues that derives_from mesenchymal tissue.

name: large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma
description: A lung large cell carcinoma that derives_from neuroendocrine cells.

name: follicular lymphoma
description: A B-cell lymphoma that is characterized as an indolent non-Hodgkin's lymphoma and has_material_basis_in follicle center B-cells (centrocytes and centroblasts).

name: obsolete small cell neuroendocrine carcinoma of the lung
Caroli disease
description: A bile duct disease that is characterized by abnormal dilatation of the intrahepatic bile ducts.

name: pancreatic agenesis
description: A pancreas disease that is characterized by the failure of the pancreas to develop prior to birth.

name: fragile X-associated tremor/ataxia syndrome
description: A X-linked hereditary ataxia that is characterized by adult-onset progressive intention tremor and gait ataxia, has_material_basis_in expanded trinucleotide repeat of the FMR1 gene that results_in a toxic gain of function of FMR1 RNA.

name: Koolen de Vries syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by developmental delay, intellectual disability, muscle weakness (hypotonia), epilepsy, distinctive facial features and congenital malformations of the heart, urogenital tract and the central nervous system, and has_material_basis_in either a chromosome 17 (17q21.31) microdeletion or a mutation in the KANSL1-gene.
synonyms: ["17q21.31 microdeletion syndrome","KANSL1-related intellectual disability syndrome","KdVS","Koolen-De Vries syndrome"]

name: inclusion body myopathy with Paget disease of bone and frontotemporal dementia
description: A syndrome that is characterized by progressive proximal muscle weakness, steolytic bone lesions consistent with Paget disease, and frontotemporal dementia and has_material_basis_in mutation in the valosin containing protein.
synonyms: ["IBMPFD","inclusion body myopathy with Paget's disease of bone and frontotemporal dementia"]

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 5
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by the early-onset of cerebellar signs and eye movement abnormalities with a very slow disease progression, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the SPTBN2 gene.

name: infantile cerebellar-retinal degeneration
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by onset between ages 2 and 6 months of truncal hypotonia, athetosis, seizures, and ophthalmologic abnormalities, particularly optic atrophy and retinal degeneration.

name: triosephosphate isomerase deficiency
description: A glucose metabolism disorder that is characterized by chronic haemolytic anaemia, cardiomyopathy, susceptibility to infections and severe neurological dysfunction, and has_material_basis_in the triosephosphate isomerase enzyme (TPI1) gene inherited as an autosomal recessive trait.

name: IMAGe syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by intrauterine growth restriction, metaphyseal dysplasia, adrenal hypoplasia congenita, genital abnormalities and has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the CDKN1C gene.
synonyms: ["intrauterine growth restriction, metaphyseal dysplasia, adrenal hypoplasia congenita, genital abnormalities"]

name: Troyer syndrome
description: A hereditary spastic paraplegia that is characterized by spasticity of the leg muscles, progressive muscle weakness, paraplegia, muscle wasting in the hands and feet (distal amyotrophy), small stature, developmental delay, learning disorders, speech difficulties (dysarthria), and mood swings, and has_material_basis_in a mutation of the SPG20 gene.
synonyms: ["autosomal recessive spastic paraplegia 20","autosomal recessive spastic paraplegia Troyer type","autosomal recessive spastic paraplegia type 20","childhood-onset spastic paraparesis with distal muscle wasting","hereditary spastic paraplegia 20","spastic paraplegia 20","spastic paraplegia type 20","SPG20"]

name: Townes-Brocks syndrome
description: A syndrome that is characterized by imperforate anus, dysplastic ears often associated with sensorineural and/or conductive hearing impairment, and thumb malformations.

name: syndromic intellectual disability
description: An intellectual disability that is characterized by the presence of associated medical and behavioral sign and symptoms.

name: non-syndromic intellectual disability
description: An intellectual disability that is characterized by the absence of associated medical and behavioral signs and symptoms.

name: synucleinopathy
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by the abnormal accumulation of aggregates of alpha-synuclein protein in neurons, nerve fibres or glial cells.

name: adrenal cortical adenoma
description: An adrenal adenoma that is a benign tumor of the adrenal cortex.

name: adrenal gland pheochromocytoma
description: A malignant pheochromocytoma that is characterized by overproduction of adrenaline.

name: gallbladder adenoma
description: A gallbladder benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin located_in the gallbladder.

name: ameloblastoma
description: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in odontogenic epithelium.

name: bone ameloblastoma
description: A bone benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in odontogenic epithelium and is located_in bone.

name: bone squamous cell carcinoma
description: A bone carcinoma that derives_from squamous epithelial cells.

name: bone chondrosarcoma
description: A chondrosarcoma that is located_in bone.

name: phalanx chondroma
description: A bone benign neoplasm that is located_in the phalanx that has_material_basis_in cartilaginous cells.

name: brain stem medulloblastoma
description: A brain stem cancer that begins in the lower part of the brain on the floor of the skull.

name: sacrum chordoma
description: A spinal chordoma that is located_in the sacrum.

name: corpus callosum oligodendroglioma
description: A brain oligodendroglioma located_in the corpus callosum.

name: medulloblastoma
description: An infratentorial cancer that is located_in the lower part of the brain and is a type of primitive neuroectodermal tumor.
synonyms: ["brain medulloblastoma","CNS PNET","CPNET","infratentorial primitive neuroectodermal tumor","localized primitive neuroectodermal tumor"]

name: parietal lobe ependymoma
description: A parietal lobe neoplasm that has_material_basis_in cells lining the ventricles of the brain.

name: salivary gland carcinoma
description: A salivary gland cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: inflammatory myofibroblastic tumor
description: A mesenchymal cell neoplasm that has_material_basis_in myofibroblastic cells admixed with inflammatory cells.

name: conjunctival nevus
description: A sensory organ benign neoplasm that is located in the eye conjunctiva.

name: mixed extragonadal germ cell cancer
description: A mixed germ cell cancer that is located_in areas of the body other than the ovary or testicle.

name: myelodysplastic syndrome
description: A bone marrow cancer that is characterized by under production of white blood cells, red blood cells and platelets.

name: MALT lymphoma
description: A marginal zone B-cell lymphoma that has_material_basis_in mucosal tissue involved in antibody production.

name: cecum adenoma
description: A cecal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: appendix carcinoid tumor
description: An appendix cancer that has_material_basis_in neurodendocrine cells.

name: colon adenoma
description: A colonic benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: large intestine adenocarcinoma
description: A large intestine cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: large intestine adenoma
description: An intestinal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin and is located_in the large intestine.

name: rectum adenoma
description: An rectal neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: bronchus mucoepidermoid carcinoma
description: A bronchus cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells, mucus-secreting cells, and intermediate cells.

name: lung combined type small cell adenocarcinoma
description: A lung combined type small cell carcinoma that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue of glandular origin.

name: vaginal carcinoma
description: A vaginal cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: trachea mucoepidermoid carcinoma
description: A trachea carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of squamous cells, mucus-secreting cells, and intermediate cells.

name: tonsil squamous cell carcinoma
description: A tonsil cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: pharynx squamous cell carcinoma
description: A pharynx cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells.

name: gastrointestinal carcinoma
description: A gastrointestinal system cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

name: spindle epithelial tumor with thymus-like differentiation tumor
description: A thyroid gland carcinoma that has_material_basis_in compact bundles of long spindle epithelial cells that merge with tubulopapillary structures and/or mucinous glands.
synonyms: ["SETTLE tumor","SETTLE tumour","spindle epithelial tumour with thymus-like differentiation tumour"]

name: striated muscle rhabdoid tumor
description: A muscle cancer that is located_in striated muscle and has_material_basis_in rhabdoid cells which are large cells with eccentrically located nuclei and abundant, eosinophilic cytoplasm.

name: small intestine carcinoid neuroendocrine tumor
description: A small intestine cancer that has_material_basis_in cells of the neuroendocrine system.

name: jejunal adenocarcinoma
description: A jejunal cancer that is located_in the jejunum and has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue that has glandular origin.

name: duodenum adenoma
description: A duodenal benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue with glandular origin.

name: ovarian melanoma
description: An ovarian cancer that has_material_basis_in melanoctyes.

name: mucosal melanoma
description: A melanoma that has_material_basis_in melanocytes located_in mucosal membranes lining the respiratory, gastrointestinal and urogenital tract.

name: sublingual gland adenoid cystic carcinoma
description: A sublingual gland cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures within the affected organ.

name: parotid gland adenoid cystic carcinoma
description: A parotid gland cancer that is characterized by a distinctive pattern in which abnormal nests or cords of epithelial cells surround and/or infiltrate ducts or glandular structures within the affected organ.

name: lung mucoepidermoid carcinoma
description: A lung carcinoma that has_material_basis in a combination of squamous cells, mucus secreting cells and intermediate cells.

name: ovarian serous carcinoma
description: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in the lining of the ovary and produces a serum-like fluid.

name: ovarian clear cell carcinoma
description: An ovarian carcinoma that has_material_basis_in cells with clear cytoplasm and glycogen secreting hob nail cells.

name: cervical neuroblastoma
description: An extracranial neuroblastoma that has_material_basis_in immature nerve cells.

name: extra-adrenal pheochromocytoma
description: A malignant pheochromocytoma that originate in the ganglia of the sympathetic nervous system and are named based upon the primary anatomical site of origin.

name: retroperitoneal neuroblastoma
description: A retroperitoneal cancer that has_material_basis_in immature nerve cells.

name: breast lobular carcinoma
description: A breast carcinoma that derives_from breast lobules (milk glands).

name: uterine corpus endometrial carcinoma
description: A uterine corpus cancer that is derives_from the inner lining of the uterus.

name: endocervical adenocarcinoma
description: An endocervical carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

name: spastic ataxia 2
description: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar ataxia, spasticity and peripheral neuropathy in the first two decades of life, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KIF1C gene on chromosome 17p13.

name: spastic ataxia 3
description: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar ataxia, spasticity, hyperreflexia, urinary urgency and dysarthria, has_material_basis_in  homozygous or compound heterozygous complex genomic rearrangements involving the MARS2 gene on chromosome 2q33.

name: spastic ataxia 4
description: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar ataxia, spasticity, dysarthria and optic atrophy, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the MTPAP gene on chromosome 10p11.

name: spastic ataxia 5
description: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by early onset of cerebellar ataxia, spasticity, oculomotor apraxia, dystonia and myoclonic epilepsy, has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the AFG3L2 gene on chromosome 18p11.

name: spastic ataxia 7
description: A spastic ataxia that is characterized by poor visual acuity, cerebellar ataxia, dysarthria and pyramidal signs.

name: Charlevoix-Saguenay spastic ataxia
description: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by early onset of cerebellar ataxia, pyramidal tract signs and peripheral neuropathy, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the gene encoding the sacsin protein on chromosome 13q12.

name: hereditary hypophosphatemic rickets with hypercalciuria
description: A rickets that has_material_basis_in increased serum 1,25-dihydroxyvitamin D levels and increased intestinal calcium absorption and is characterized by the presence of hypophosphatemia secondary to renal phosphate wasting, radiographic and/or histologic evidence of rickets, limb deformities, muscle weakness, and bone pain.

name: autosomal dominant hypophosphatemic rickets
description: A rickets characterized by low levels of serum phosphate and elevated levels of ALP and phosphaturia and that has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: autosomal recessive hypophosphatemic rickets
description: A rickets that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance mutation in the DMP1 gene and is characterized by hypophosphatemia, rickets and/or osteomalacia and slow growth.

name: autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia
description: A cerebellar ataxia that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: hereditary ataxia
description: A neurodegenerative disease that is characterized by slowly progressive incoordination of gait and often associated with poor coordination of hands, speech, and eye movements.

name: spastic ataxia
description: A hereditary ataxia that is characterized by early onset of cerebellar ataxia, pyramidal tract signs and peripheral neuropathy.

name: X-linked hereditary ataxia
description: A hereditary ataxia that is characterized by X-linked inheritance.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 1
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, dysarthria, dysphagia, dystonia and peripheral neuropathy that begins in early adulthood, has_material_basis_in the expanded (CAG)n trinucleotide repeat of ataxin-1 gene on chromosome 6p22.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 2
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, bulbar palsy, peripheral neuropathy chorea and muscle atrophy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATXN2 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 6
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progresive ataxia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the CACNA1A gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 4
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progresive ataxia, dysarthria and peripheral neuropathy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the SCA4 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 7
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, progressive vision loss, and failure to thrive, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATXN7 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 8
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive dysarthria, bradykinesia, nystagmus and loss of coordination, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATXN80S gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 10
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by gait ataxia, upper-limb ataxia, dysarthria and dysphagia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATXN10 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 11
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, nystagmus, pyramidal abonormalities and peripheral neuropathy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the TTBK2 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 12
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by minor ataxia and intention tremor, has_material_basis_in CAG expansion of the PPP2R2B gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 13
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by developmental delay, ataxia, myoclinic jerks, dysarthria, dysphagia and seizure, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the KCNC3 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 14
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, dysarthria and dysphagia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the PRKCG gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 15
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, nystagmus, dysarthria and dysphagia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ITPR1 gene.

name: obsolete spinocerebellar ataxia type 16
description: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by truncal and limb ataxia, dysarthria, nystagmus, peripheral neuropathy and limb spasticity, has_material_basis_in mutation in the STUB1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 17
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by chorea, dementia, dystonia, spasiticity and seizure, has_material_basis_in CAG repeat expansion in the TBP gene.

name: autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia, deafness and narcolepsy
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, sensorineal deafness, narcolepsy with cataplexy, and dementia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the DNMT1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 18
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar ataxia and sensory neuropathy, has_material_basis_in mutation on chromosome 7q22-q23.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 19/22
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by mild cerebellar ataxia, cognitive impairment, myoclonus and tremor.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 20
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by cerebellar dysarthria.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 21
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive cerebellar ataxia, cognitive impairment, tremor, bradykinesia and rigidity.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 23
description: An autosomal dominnant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive ataxia, dysarthria, slow saccades and hyperreflexia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the PDYN gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 25
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia and sensory neuropathy, has_material_basis_in repeat CAG expansion on chromosome 2p15-p21.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 26
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive ataxia and oculomotor abnormalities, has_material_basis_in mutation in the EEF2 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 27
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive ataxia, early-onset tremor and dyskinesia, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the FGF14 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 28
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, dysarthria, hyperreflexia, ophthalmoparesis, nystagmus and ptosis, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the AFG3L2 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 29
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, intellectual disability, dysarthria and ophthalmoplegia, and has_material_basis_in mutation in the ITPR1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 30
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive gait abnormalities and dysarthria, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ODZ3 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 31
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by late-onset ataxia, dysarthria and horizontal nystagmus, has_material_basis_in repeat expansion mutation in the BEAN1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 34
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by papulosquamous, ichthyosiform plaques at birth and progressive ataxia, dysarthria, nystagmus and hyporeflexia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ELOVL4 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 35
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by a slowly progressive ataxia, tremor, dysarthria and hyperreflexia, has_material_basis_in mutation in the TGM6 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 36
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia, dysarthria, hyperreflexia, sensiorineural hearing loss and muscle atrophy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the NOP56 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 37
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive ataxia and dysarthria, presenting in mid-adulthood, and has_material_basis_in mutation to the DAB1 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 38
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by slowly progressive ataxia and nystagmus, presenting in mid-adulthood, and has_material_basis_in mutation to the ELOVL5 gene.

name: spinocerebellar ataxia type 40
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by progressive gait abnormalutes, dysarthria, tremor and hyporeflexia, has_material_basis_in muation in the CCDC88C gene.

name: hypomyelinating leukoencephalopathy
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by nystagmus, spasticity, and a distinct pattern of MRI abnormalities.

name: GRID2-related spinocerebellar ataxia
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by cognitive delay, abnormal eye movements, and hearing loss.

name: episodic ataxia type 1
description: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by periodic ataxia and frequent myokymic discharges, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the potassium channel gene KCNA1.

name: episodic ataxia type 2
description: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by periodic ataxia and nystagmus, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the calcium channel gene CACNA1A.

name: episodic ataxia type 3
description: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by periodic ataxia, myokymia, vertigo and tinnitus, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: episodic ataxia type 4
description: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by vertigo and diplopia.

name: episodic ataxia type 5
description: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by dysarthria and vertigo, develops in early childhood, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the CACNB4 gene.

name: episodic ataxia type 6
description: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by nystagmus and dysarthria, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the SLC1A3 gene.

name: episodic ataxia type 7
description: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by episodes of weakness and dysarthria, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.

name: episodic ataxia type 8
description: An episodic ataxia that is characterized by weakness, dysarthria and myokymia, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the UBR4 gene.

name: cerebellar ataxia, mental retardation and dysequlibrium syndrome
description: An syndrome characterized by congenital onset of nonprogressive cerebellar ataxia, disturbed equilibrium, and mental retardation, associated with cerebellar hypoplasia.
synonyms: ["CAMRQ","Cerebellar Ataxia, Mental Retardation, and Dysequilibrium Syndrome 1 (CAMRQ1)","Uner Tan syndrome","VLDLR Cerebellar Hypoplasia"]

name: nonprogressive cerebellar ataxia with mental retardation
description: An autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by early onset of nonprogressive cerebellar ataxia, developmental delay, intellectual impairment and cerebellar atrophy, and has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of mutation in the CAMTA1 gene.

name: autosomal recessive spinocerebellar ataxia 10
description: An autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia that is characterized by ataxia, dysarthria, nystagmus and marked cerebellar atrophy, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ANO10 gene.

name: infective endocarditis
description: An endocarditis that is characterized by inflammation of the endocardium caused by infectious agents.

name: withdrawal disorder
description: A substance-related disorder that occurs upon the abrupt discontinuation/separation or a decrease in dosage of the intake of medications, recreational drugs, and alcohol.

name: C1 inhibitor deficiency
description: A complement deficiency that is a functional deficiency in the complement component C1 inhibitor leading to hereditary angioedema (HAE) involving swelling due to leakage of fluid from blood vessels into connective tissue.

name: autoimmune disease of central nervous system
description: An autoimmune hypersensitivity disease located_in the central nervous system.

name: autoimmune disease of endocrine system
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system resulting in production of antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the endocrine system.

name: obsolete artemis deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is caused when the DCLREI1, DNA cross-link repair 1C gene contains mutations resulting in the inability to repair DNA.

name: CD3zeta deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that affects the development and function of T cells.

name: janus kinase-3 deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is characterized by severe cell-mediated and antibody-mediated immunodeficiency with recurrent bacterial, viral, and fungal infections, develops_from janus kinase-3 deficiency, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the JAK3 gene of chromosome 19p13.11, responsible for normal differentiation and maturation of B and T immune cells.

name: MHC class I deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial, viral, and fungal infections, especially of the lung, and sterile necrotizing granulomas of the skin, develops_from deficiency or decreased surface expression of MHC Class I, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation affecting MHC Class I production or expression and frequently involves TAP1 and TAP2 subunits, and is typically asymptomatic in infancy.
synonyms: ["bare lymphocyte syndrome type I","BLS, TYPE I","BLSI","HLA CLASS I DEFICIENCY"]

name: Omenn syndrome
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that has_material_basis in the RAG1 and RAG2 genes on chromosome 11p and the Artemis gene on chromosome 10p. It is characterized by erythroderma, desquamation, alopecia, chronic diarrhea, failure to thrive, lymphadenopathy, and hepatosplenomegaly.

name: recombinase activating gene 1 deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the result of a mutation on Chromosome 6 RAG1 gene involving genetic rearrangement of both the T- and B-lymphocyte receptor genes.

name: recombinase activating gene 2 deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the result of a mutation on Chromosome 6 RAG2 gene involving genetic rearrangement of both the T- and B-lymphocyte receptor genes.

name: X-linked severe combined immunodeficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is a X-linked SCID that has_material_basis_in mutations in genes encoding common gamma chain proteins shared by the interleukin (IL-2,4,7,9,16 and21) receptors resulting in a non-functional gamma chain, defective interleukin signalling, minimal or ascent T- and NK cells and non-functional B-cells.
synonyms: ["gamma chain deficiency","SCID-X1","thymic epithelial hypoplasia","X-Linked Severe Combined Immunodeficiency","XSCID"]

name: CD45 deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is an autosomal recessive disease with T and B lymphocyte dysfunction, due to a large deletion at one allelle and a point mutation at the other. The point mutation resulted in the alteration of intervening sequence 13 donor splice site. The population of T lymphocytes is diminished and unresponsive to mitogen stimulation. The level of B lymphocyte numbers, serum immunoglobulin decreased with age.

name: interleukin-7 receptor alpha deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that results from defective IL7R expression causes T-B+NK+ SCID. Loss of IL-7R function leads to the loss of an antiapoptotic signal, resulting in a loss of T-cell selection in thymus.

name: CD3delta deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is characterized by the absence of T cells but normal numbers of B cells. CD3D is essential for T cell development.

name: CD3epsilon deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive mutations in the gene coding for T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3epsilon chain precursors. Patients with CD3epsilon deficiency have a severe defect in the expression of the T-cell receptor CD3-complex.

name: CD3gamma deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive mutations in the gene coding for T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3gamma chain precursors.  Patients with CD3gamma deficiency have a severe defect in the expression of the T-cell receptor CD3-complex. Affected patients have decreased T-cell numbers and function; B cells are variably affected.

name: coronin-1A deficiency
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is an actin regulator when mutated results in SCID through inhibition of thymic egress of mature thymocytes into peripheral lymphoid organs.

name: reticular dysgenesis
description: A severe combined immunodeficiency that is the most severe form of SCID and has_material_basis_in mutations in the gene encoding mitochondrial adenylate kinase 2. It is characterized by congenital agranulocytosis, lymphopenia, and lymphoid and thymic hypoplasia with absent cellular and humoral immunity functions.

name: DNA ligase IV deficiency
description: A combined T cell and B cell immunodeficiency that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the LIG4 gene, a DNA ligase, encoding a protein essential for V(D)J recombination and DNA double-strand break (DSB) repair through nonhomologous end joining (NHEJ). Patients present with immunodeficiency and developmental and growth delay.

name: CD40 ligand deficiency
description: A combined T cell and B cell immunodeficiency that is a X-linked immunodeficiency with hyperimmunoglobulin M (XHIM) affecting isotype switching and is caused by the absence of CD40 ligand which is normally expressed on activated CD4+ T cells. Individuals with this mutation are unable to switch from IgM to IgG, IgA and IgE.

name: immunodeficiency with hyper IgM type 3
description: A hyper IgM syndrome that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TNFRSF5 gene, resulting in type 3 hyper-IgM immunodeficiency that is characterized by an inability of B cells to undergo isotype switching, an inability to mount an antibody-specific immune response, and a lack of germinal center formation.
synonyms: ["CD40 deficiency","hyper-IgM syndrome due to CD40 deficiency","type 3 hyper-IgM immunodeficiency"]

name: lambda 5 deficiency
description: A B cell deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutations in the IGLL1 gene. Lambda 5 mutations can cause a block in B cell development at the transition between the pro-B cell and the pre-B cell stage.

name: immunoglobulin alpha deficiency
description: A B cell deficiency that is an autosomal recessive disorder that has_material_basis_in mutation in the IgA (CD79 alpha) antigen receptor.

name: immunoglobulin beta deficiency
description: A B cell deficiency that is characterized by mucosal infections and autoimmune diseases due to lack of production of immunoglobulin A antibody, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance.

name: agammaglobulinemia 4
description: An agammaglobulinemia that has_material_basis_in a mutation a homozygous mutation in the BLNK gene on chromosome 10q23.2.
synonyms: ["B cell linker protein deficiency","B-cell linker protein deficiency","BLNK deficiency"]

name: Good syndrome
description: A combined T cell and B cell immunodeficiency that is a condition where there is co-occurrence of deficient cell-mediated immunity and benign thymoma.

name: autoimmune disease of exocrine system
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the exocrine system.

name: autoimmune disease of eyes, ear, nose and throat
description: An autoimmune disease located_in eyes, located_in ears, located_in nose and located_in throat.

name: autoimmune disease of gastrointestinal tract
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the gastrointestinal tract.

name: autoimmune disease of musculoskeletal system
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the musculoskeletal system.

name: autoimmune disease of peripheral nervous system
description: An autoimmune disease of the nervous system that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the peripheral nervous system.

name: obsolete medical disorder
description: A disease that is present at birth due to a genetic abnormality, error with embryonic development, infection or compromised intrauterine environment.

name: intrinsic cardiomyopathy
description: A cardiomyopathy that is characterized as weakness in the muscle of the heart that is not due to an identifiable external cause.

name: developmental disorder of mental health
description: A disease of mental health that occur during a child's developmental period between birth and age 18 resulting in retarding of the child's psychological or physical development.

name: specific developmental disorder
description: A developmental disorder of mental health that categorizes specific learning disabilities and developmental disorders affecting coordination.

name: autoimmune disease of skin and connective tissue
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the skin and connective tissue.

name: pervasive developmental disorder
description: A developmental disorder of mental health that refers to a group of five disorders characterized by impairments in socialization and communication, as well as restricted interests and repetitive behaviors.

name: autism spectrum disorder
description: A pervasive developmental disorder that is a spectrum of psychological conditions. The disease has_symptom widespread abnormalities of social interactions and communication, has_symptom severely restricted interests and has_symptom highly repetitive behavior.

name: atypical autism
description: An autism spectrum disorder that involves some autistic symptoms occuring after age 3 with an abscence of all the traits necessary for a diagnosis of autism.

name: sexual disorder
description: A disease of mental health that involves the impairment in normal sexual functioning.

name: paraphilia disorder
description: A sexual disorder that is characterized recurrent, intense sexually arousing fantasies, sexual urges or behaviors generally involving nonhuman objects.

name: Munchausen by proxy
description: A factitious disorder that involves a care giver's deliberate exaggeration, fabrication, and/or induce physical, psychological, behavioral, and/or mental health problems in others.

name: aphasia
description: A language disorder that involves an acquired impairment of any laguage modality such as producting or comprehending spoken or written language.

name: writing disorder
description: A learning disability that involves impaired written language ability such as impairments in handwriting, spelling, organization of ideas, and composition.

name: nosophobia
description: A specific phobia that involves an irrational fear of contracting a disease.

name: autoimmune disease of urogenital tract
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the urogenital tract.

name: autoimmune disease of blood
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the blood.

name: autoimmune disease of cardiovascular system
description: An autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or T cells against cells and/or tissues in the cardiovascular system.

name: obsolete neurological disorder
description: A physical disorder that is the result of structural, biochemical or electrical abnormalities in the brain or spinal cord, or in the nerves leading to or from them, can result in symptoms such as paralysis, muscle weakness, poor coordination, loss of sensation, seizures, confusion, pain and altered levels of consciousness.

name: obsolete peripheral neuropathy
description: A neuropathy that is located_in nerves of the peripheral nervous system.

name: autonomic peripheral neuropathy
description: A neuropathy that affects the autonomic nervous system and is characterized by urinary incontinence, gastrointestinal dysmotility, orthostatic hypotension, apneas, sweat disturbances and impotence.

name: popliteal pterygium syndrome
description: A syndrome characterized by abnormal development of the face, skin and genitals. Clinical expressions of the disease include cleft lip, with or without cleft palate, contractures of the lower extremities, abnormal external genitalia, syndactyly of fingers and/or toes, and a pyramidal skin fold over the hallux nail. It has_material_basis_in mutations in the IRF6 gene on chromosome 1.

name: hypersensitivity reaction disease
description: An immune system disease that has_material_basis_in abnormal immune responses.

name: gluten allergy
description: A food allergy to wheat that is characterized by stomach cramping, diarrhea and gastrointestinal upset and is unrelated to the gluten intolerance.

name: lymphoma
description: A hematologic cancer that affects lymphocytes that reside in the lymphatic system and in blood-forming organs.

name: non-Hodgkin lymphoma
description: A lymphoma that is characterized as any kind of lymphoma except Hodgkin's lymphoma.

name: cutaneous T cell lymphoma
description: A non-Hodgkin's lymphoma that has_material_basis_in a mutation of T cells.

name: familial juvenile hyperuricemic nephropathy
description: A kidney disease that is characterized by hyperuricemia with renal uric acid under-excretion, gout and chronic kidney disease.

name: sideroblastic anemia 1
description: A sideoblastic anemia that is characterized by the presence of microcytic hypochromic anemia and iron overload, and has_material_basis_in X-linked inheritance of mutation in the ALAS2 gene that enocdes aminolevulinic acid synthase that catalyzes the first step in heme production.

name: obsolete sideroblastic anemia with spinocerebellar ataxia
description: A sideoblastic anemia that is characterized by microcytic hypochromic anemia and ealy-onset, slowly progressive spinocerebellar ataxia, and has_material_basis_in X-linked inheritance of mutation in the ABCB7 gene that encodes a transporter protein that plays a role in heme production in the bone marrow and cerebellum.

name: autosomal recessive pyridoxine-refractory sideroblastic anemia 2
description: A sideroblastic anemia that is characterized by microcytic hypochromic anemia and iron overload, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the SLC25A38 gene.
synonyms: ["autosomal recessive pyridoxine-refractory sideroblastic anaemia 2","pyridoxine-refractory autosomal recessive sideroblastic anaemia","pyridoxine-refractory autosomal recessive sideroblastic anemia"]

name: pyridoxine-responsive sideroblastic anemia
description: A sideoblastic anemia that is characterized by the presence of microcytic hypochromic anemia and iron overload, and has_material_basis_in X-linked inheritance.

name: Pearson syndrome
description: A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by sideroblastic anemia and exocrine pancreas dysfunction.

name: nonbacterial thrombotic endocarditis
description: An endocarditis that results from the deposition of small sterile vegetations on valve leaflets.

name: pre-malignant neoplasm
description: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body, which do not invade or destroy the surrounding tissue but, given enough time, will transform into a cancer.

name: benign neoplasm
description: A disease of cellular proliferation that results in abnormal growths in the body which lack the ability to metastasize.

name: lymphatic system cancer
description: An immune system cancer that is located_in the lymphatic system and is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of lymphoid tissue.

name: ductal carcinoma in situ
description: A breast carcinoma in situ that is characterized by being non-invasive, not having spread outside of the duct into the surrounding breast tissue, has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells, derives_from epithelial cells.

name: estrogen-receptor positive breast cancer
description: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of estrogen receptors.

name: estrogen-receptor negative breast cancer
description: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of estrogen receptors.

name: progesterone-receptor positive breast cancer
description: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of progesterone receptors.

name: progesterone-receptor negative breast cancer
description: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of progesterone receptors.

name: Her2-receptor positive breast cancer
description: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of Her2 receptors.

name: Her2-receptor negative breast cancer
description: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of Her2 receptors.

name: triple-receptor negative breast cancer
description: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of estrogen, progresterone and Her2 receptors.

name: breast benign neoplasm
description: A thoracic benign neoplasm that is characterized by lack of malignancy.

name: immune system cancer
description: An organ system cancer located_in the immune system that is characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation in organs of the immune system.

name: cell type benign neoplasm
description: A benign neoplasm that is classified by the type of cell or tissue from which it is derived.

name: organ system benign neoplasm
description: A benign neoplasm that is classified by the organ system from which it is arising from.

name: female reproductive organ benign neoplasm
description: A reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is characterized by a lack of malignancy located_in the female reproductive system.

name: male reproductive organ benign neoplasm
description: A reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is characterized by a lack of malignancy located_in the male reproductive system.

name: vestibular gland benign neoplasm
description: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the vestibular gland.

name: endocrine organ benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in endocrine glands which secretes a type of hormone directly into the bloodstream to regulate the body.

name: central nervous system benign neoplasm
description: A nervous system benign neoplasm that is characterized by lack of malignancy.

name: cardiovascular organ benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm disease located_in the blood, heart, blood vessels or the lymphatic system.

name: immune system organ benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm located_in the immune system organs.

name: bone benign neoplasm
description: A connective tissue benign neoplasm that is located_in bone.

name: uterine benign neoplasm
description: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the uterus.

name: sensory organ benign neoplasm
description: A nervous system benign neoplasm that is located_in a sensory organ.

name: thoracic benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplam that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

name: osteoblastoma
description: A bone benign neoplasm of the bone that is characterized by clinical and histological similarity to osteoid osteomas.

name: musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the muscular and skeletal organs.

name: musculoskeletal system cancer
description: An organ system cancer located_in the muscular and skeletal organs and characterized by uncontrolled cellular proliferation of the musculoskeletal organs.

name: obsolete benign glioma
description: A cell type benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in glial cells.

name: cartilage cancer
description: A connective tissue tumor that can be a benign chondroma or a maligannt chondrosarcoma.

name: central nervous system primitive neuroectodermal neoplasm
description: A central nervous system cancer of children and young adults that develops from neural crest cells located_in cerebrum, has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from neuroectoderm.

name: cerebellar medulloblastoma
description: A cerebellum cancer that begins in the lower part of the brain on the floor of the skull.

name: brain meningioma
description: A brain cancer that is characterized by tumor of the meninges, that develops from the membranes that surround the brain and spinal cord, has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from meningeal cells of embryonic ectoderm origin.

name: brain glioma
description: A brain cancer that has_material_basis_in glial cells.

name: vulvar benign neoplasm
description: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the vulva.

name: cervical benign neoplasm
description: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the cervix.

name: fallopian tube benign neoplasm
description: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the fallopian tube.

name: ovarian benign neoplasm
description: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the ovary.

name: vaginal benign neoplasm
description: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the vagina.

name: nervous system benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the central nervous system or located_in the peripheral nervous system.

name: sensory system cancer
description: A nervous system cancer that is located in the sensory system.

name: peritoneal benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the serous membrane lining the abdominal cavity or coelom.

name: thoracic disease
description: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

name: pharynx cancer
description: A gastrointestinal system cancer that is located_in the pharynx.

name: integumentary system benign neoplasm
description: An organ system benign neoplasm located_in the integumentary system organs.

name: integumentary system cancer
description: An organ system cancer that is located_in the skin, hair and nails.

name: connective tissue benign neoplasm
description: A musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm that is located_in connective tissue.
synonyms: ["mesenchymal tissue neoplasm","neoplasm of soft tissue","neoplasm of soft tissues","soft tissue benign neoplasm","tumor of the soft tissue"]

name: heavy chain disease
description: A hypersensitivity reaction type IV disease that results from a proliferation of cells producing immunoglobulin heavy chains.

name: alpha chain disease
description: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of alpha antibodies (IgA).

name: gamma heavy chain disease
description: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of gamma antibody (IgG).

name: mu chain disease
description: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of mu antibody (IgM).

name: delta chain disease
description: A heavy chain disease that results from an overproduction of delta antibody (IgD).

name: akinetopsia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of motion perception.

name: alexithymia
description: An agnosia that is a deficiency in understanding, processing, or describing emotions.

name: amusia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize musical notes, rhythms, and intervals.

name: anosognosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to gain feedback about one's own condition or impairments.

name: apperceptive agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguish visual shapes.

name: apraxia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to map out physical actions in order to repeat them in functional activities.

name: associative agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize visual scenes or classes of objects but retain the abilty to describe them.

name: auditory agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguishing environmental and non-verbal auditory cues including difficulty distinguishing speech from non-speech sounds even though hearing is usually normal.

name: autotopagnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to orient parts of the body.

name: color agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize a color, while being able to perceive or distinguish it.

name: cortical deafness
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive any auditory information but whose hearing is intact.

name: finger agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to distinguish the fingers on the hand.

name: form agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive a whole object while perceiving only parts of details.

name: integrative agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to integrate these elements together into comprehensible perceptual wholes while recognizing elements of the whole.

name: mirror agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to acknowledge objects in the neglected field that are visible when a mirror reflects the object visible in the non-neglected field.

name: pain agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive and process pain.

name: phonagnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize familiar voices.

name: semantic agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to visually recognise an object while maintaining the use of non-visual sensory systems such as feeling, tapping, smelling, rocking or flicking the object to recognise the object.

name: simultanagnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recgonize a whole image or scene while retianing the ability to recognize objects or details in their visual field one at a time.

name: social emotional agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to perceive facial expression, body language and intonation, rendering them unable to non-verbally perceive people's emotions and limiting that aspect of social interaction.

name: astereognosia
description: An agnosia that is the loss of the ability to recognize objects by touch based on its texture, size and weight.

name: tactile agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize or identify objects by touch alone.

name: time agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to comprehend the succession and duration of events.

name: topographical agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to rely on visual cues to guide them directionally due to the inability to recognise objects.

name: verbal auditory agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognising spoken words as semantically meaningful.

name: visual agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to visually recognize objects.

name: visual verbal agnosia
description: An agnosia that is a loss of the ability to comprehending the meaning of written words.

name: diffuse alopecia areata
